    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-07-01T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-07-01T11:00:00-05:00" n="854"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d854">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 841.711/2530</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Great Britain</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LIB1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Laughlin</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-07-01T17:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 1, 1918, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received July 1, 3.15 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>18. Your 8508, June 29, 3 p.m. All outgoing American pouches are carried by
                    Embassy messenger from the Embassy to the steamer and ail incoming pouches are
                    delivered into his custody on the steamer on her arrival, the port authorities
                    granting all facilities. The British postal administration does not handle them
                    in any way.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LIB1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Laughlin</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
